---
import AppLayout from '../layouts/AppLayout.astro';
---

<AppLayout
  title="ListIPs - Firewall IP List Publishing"
  description="Create, validate, sync, and publish clean IP/CIDR allowlists and blocklists for firewalls, scripts, and edge automation."
  canonicalPath="/"
>
  <main class="home-page">
    <header class="marketing-nav">
      <a class="brand-lockup" href="/" aria-label="ListIPs home">
        <img class="brand-logo" src="/images/logo.png" alt="ListIPs" width="300" height="73" decoding="sync" fetchpriority="high" />
      </a>
      <nav class="nav-actions" aria-label="Primary">
        <a id="home-auth-link" class="button primary small" href="/login">Sign in</a>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <section class="home-hero">
      <div class="hero-copy">
        <p class="eyebrow">Firewall list publishing</p>
        <h1>Publish firewall IP lists your stack can trust.</h1>
        <p class="lede">
          Build allowlists, blocklists, and vendor ranges in one place. ListIPs validates every line, syncs approved sources, and publishes raw text endpoints that firewalls and scripts can consume without extra glue.
        </p>
        <div class="home-actions">
          <a class="button primary" href="/login">Login with GitHub</a>
          <a class="button secondary" href="https://github.com/VIWEB-TECHNOLOGY/ListIPs" rel="noopener noreferrer">Open source on GitHub</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <section class="product-preview" aria-label="ListIPs dashboard preview">
        <div class="preview-toolbar">
          <span class="preview-dot"></span>
          <strong>office-allowlist</strong>
          <span>Private token URL</span>
        </div>
        <div class="preview-grid">
          <aside class="preview-list">
            <span class="preview-item active">Office Allowlist <small>5 entries</small></span>
            <span class="preview-item">Edge Blocklist <small>4 entries</small></span>
            <span class="preview-item">Vendor Ranges <small>12 entries</small></span>
          </aside>
          <div class="preview-editor">
            <div class="preview-meta">
              <span>Validated output</span>
              <strong>Ready</strong>
            </div>
            <pre><code># Office ranges
192.0.2.10
198.51.100.0/24
# VPN exit
2001:db8::/32</code></pre>
            <div class="preview-url">
              <span>Raw URL</span>
              <code>listips.com/u/acme/office-allowlist?token=sec_...</code>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </section>

    <section class="value-strip" aria-label="ListIPs capabilities">
      <div>
        <strong>Open source</strong>
        <span>ListIPs is released under the MIT License at <a href="https://github.com/VIWEB-TECHNOLOGY/ListIPs" rel="noopener noreferrer">VIWEB-TECHNOLOGY/ListIPs</a>.</span>
      </div>
      <div>
        <strong>Clean raw output</strong>
        <span>Only comments and valid IPv4, IPv6, and CIDR lines are published.</span>
      </div>
      <div>
        <strong>Private or public delivery</strong>
        <span>Use public URLs or one-time-visible private token endpoints.</span>
      </div>
      <div>
        <strong>Source sync built in</strong>
        <span>Pull approved upstream ranges and keep firewall clients on cached edge URLs.</span>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="cloudflare-native-band" aria-labelledby="cloudflare-native-title">
      <div class="cloudflare-copy">
        <p class="eyebrow">Cloudflare native</p>
        <h2 id="cloudflare-native-title">Built for edge-hosted firewall automation.</h2>
        <p>
          ListIPs runs on Cloudflare's developer platform: static frontend, Worker API, edge-cached raw delivery, managed storage, background sync, and rate limiting.
        </p>
        <div class="cloudflare-buttons" aria-label="Cloudflare project links">
          <a href="https://cloudflare.com" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            <img src="https://workers.cloudflare.com/built-with-cloudflare.svg" alt="Built with Cloudflare" width="152" height="33" loading="lazy" />
          </a>
          <a href="https://deploy.workers.cloudflare.com/?url=https://github.com/VIWEB-TECHNOLOGY/ListIPs" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            <img src="https://deploy.workers.cloudflare.com/button" alt="Deploy to Cloudflare" width="165" height="33" loading="lazy" />
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <ul class="cloudflare-services" aria-label="Cloudflare services used by ListIPs">
        <li><strong>Workers</strong><span>API and raw list delivery</span></li>
        <li><strong>Pages</strong><span>Static Astro frontend</span></li>
        <li><strong>D1</strong><span>Users, sessions, and metadata</span></li>
        <li><strong>R2</strong><span>Compiled list artifacts</span></li>
        <li><strong>Queues</strong><span>External source sync jobs</span></li>
        <li><strong>Durable Objects</strong><span>Atomic rate limits</span></li>
        <li><strong>KV</strong><span>Rate-limit fallback storage</span></li>
        <li><strong>Cron Triggers</strong><span>Scheduled sync refreshes</span></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="workflow-band">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <p class="eyebrow">How it works</p>
        <h2>Write once. Serve everywhere.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="workflow-grid">
        <article>
          <span>01</span>
          <h3>Create a list</h3>
          <p>Add manual entries, comments, and external sources for a specific firewall job.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <span>02</span>
          <h3>Validate and sync</h3>
          <p>ListIPs sanitizes output and keeps synced ranges inside the supported source policy.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <span>03</span>
          <h3>Consume the raw URL</h3>
          <p>Point HestiaCP, iptables, UFW, Nginx, or automation scripts at the edge-cached endpoint.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <footer class="site-footer">
      <span>Copyright &copy; {new Date().getFullYear()} ListIPs.</span>
      <span>By <a href="https://viweb.net" rel="noopener noreferrer">ViWeb Technology</a>.</span>
    </footer>
  </main>

  <script>
    const authLink = document.querySelector('#home-auth-link');

    fetch('/api/auth/me', { credentials: 'include' })
      .then((response) => {
        if (!response.ok || !(authLink instanceof HTMLAnchorElement)) return;
        authLink.textContent = 'Dashboard';
        authLink.href = '/dashboard/';
      })
      .catch(() => {});
  </script>
</AppLayout>
